0:Ayase Kishimoto was staring out the window, only half paying attention to anything going on around her.[%p]
100:There were no bars on the windows like there were in the rooms at Ark Heart Medical, the place she'd been before.[%p]
200:Outside, she could see the high-rise buildings of Shinjuku, and beyond them, a blazing evening sky. A few pigeons were flapping furiously across it.[%p]
300:Occasionally, she would wince in pain.[%p]
400:Her eyes were empty, and just a little tired. She wasn't humming the songs that had so entranced the young people of Shibuya.[%p]
500:After her failed suicide attempt, she'd been brought to a big general hospital in Yoyogi.[%p]
600:Her wounds had almost completely healed.[%p]
700:The doctors had said it was a miracle that a fall from that height had ended in only a few minor scrapes and bruises.[%p]
800:Still, she'd hit her head hard, so she'd been hospitalized for observation. She'd been here over a week already.[%p]
900:Of course, “observation” meant nothing more than a simple checkup once every two days. The rest of the time, she was left to herself.[%p]
1000:She had the room to herself. There were no other beds in it.[%p]
1100:Her Di-Sword was up against the window, flashing with a pale light. It'd been there the whole time she'd been here, but nobody had noticed it.[%p]
1200:She didn't get many visitors.[%p]
1300:Phantasm fans were, supposedly, coming in huge numbers every day. But the hospital had banned them from seeing her, so they wouldn't bother the other patients.[%p]
1400:She and her family weren't close. Almost nobody else came to see her.[%p]
1500:Her bandmates had come to see her once. When she'd mentioned breaking up the band, though, they'd stopped coming at all.[%p]
1600:[name]看護師[line]Kishimoto, did your thermometer go beep?[%p]
